article.headline: Finley passes for 3 TDs, runs for 2 more scores as Texas State beats Jackson State 77-34
article.description: — TJ Finley accounted for five touchdowns, including two of Texas State's eight rushing touchdowns, and the Bobcats beat Jackson State 77-34 Saturday night.

article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas -- — TJ Finley accounted for five touchdowns, including two of Texas State's eight rushing touchdowns, and the Bobcats beat Jackson State 77-34 Saturday night. Finley was 17-of-21 passing for 251 yards and connected on touchdown throws of 14 yards to Drew Donley, 27 yards to Ashtyn Hawkins and 20 yards to Kole Wilson, the last of which capped a 35-point second quarter by the Bobcats and made it 56-20 going into halftime. Texas State’s 77 points were its most since it registered a program-record 78 against Meridian College in 1920 and its 684 total yards were also its most since it had a program-record 696 against Arkansas-Pine Bluff in 2014. Malik Hornsby had 10 carries for 133 yards and two touchdowns for Texas State (2-1) and Damarius Good added 105 yards rushing on 11 carries. Ismail Mahdi opened the scoring with a 56-yard run less than a minute into the game, Donerio Davenport ran for a 9-yard touchdown and Jahmyl Jeter added two rushing TDs. Zy McDonald threw touchdown passes to Isaiah Spencer from 9-yards out and Hayden Hagler from 28 yards in the second half for Jackson State (2-2). ------ AP college football: https://apnews.com/hub/college-football and https://apnews.com/hub/ap-top-25-college-football-poll
